      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility"> ¶ I have to thank you, ¶  ¶ noble friend, ¶  ¶ for sending ¶  ¶ me ¶  ¶ the ¶  ¶ two ¶  ¶ small universal maps of Australia, from which I see that ¶  ¶ the explorations ¶  ¶ of the Daintree River, Pa...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">76.01.00</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To August Petermann</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Sammlung Perthes Archiv,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">SPA ARCH<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">PGM<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">328</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>Forschungsbibliothek Gotha der Universität Erfurt.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style=""/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Petermann: 'Erh. 24. Febr. 1876' [Received 24 February 1876]. The item is dated on the basis of M to J. MacPherson, 1 January 1876,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>which<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>mentions<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M received Thomas Elder's letter (see below) in the evening of 31 December; M must have forwarded this to Petermann in early January 1876 in order for it to reach Gotha by 24 February.</p>
                  <p rend="FootnoteText"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>For a published version of this letter, see Voigt (1996), pp. 128-9.</p>
               </note>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich habe Ihnen zu danken edler Freund, für die Zusendung der beiden kleinen Universalkarten Australiens, aus welchen ich ersehe, dass Ihnen die Forschungen vom Daintree-River, Palmer River &amp;c<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>zugänglich oder bekannt geworden sind. Wenn wir auf Ihrer neuen Karte anstatt des Planes von Sydney (der 2ten nicht der ersten Stadt Australiens) eine Zeichnung Tasmaniens bekämen, dann würde sich die Geographie Australiens auf diesem Blatt vollständig abrunden.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Über Giles's letzte merkenswerthe Reise berichte ich nicht speziell, weil Ihnen von dem nähern Schwan-Fluss aus die gedruckten Berichte schneller zukommen werden, als ich solche von hier geben kann. Das beigefügte Schreiben des braven Mr Elder wird Sie aber interessieren.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">Stets verehrungsvoll</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ihr Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have to thank you,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>noble friend,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for sending<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>me<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>two<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>small universal maps of Australia, from which I see that<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the explorations<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of the Daintree River, Palmer River<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>&amp;c<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>have<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>become<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>accessible or known to you.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to A. Petermann, 28 November 1875.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M is probably referring to the expedition in north-eastern Queensland by William Hann in 1872.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>If we could<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>have<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>drawing<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of Tasmania on your new map instead of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the town<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>plan of Sydney (the 2nd not the first city of Australia), then the geography of Australia would be rounded off completely on this sheet.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>Each of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Australien Maassstab 1:10.000.000</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="2"/>(1875) and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Australien Maassstab 1:10.000.000<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(dated 1875 but 1877?) have a map of 'Sydney and Port Jackson' at a scale of 1:150,000 inset in the Great Australian Bight (digitiseed by the National Library of Australia as<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <ref target="https://nla.gov.au/nla.obj-232625532/">https://nla.gov.au/nla.obj-232625532/</ref>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <ref target="https://nla.gov.au/nla.obj-232218071">https://nla.gov.au/nla.obj-232218071</ref>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>respectively. The equivalent map of 1869 did not include the Palmer and Daintree rivers, see <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <ref target="https://nla.gov.au/nla.obj-232223665">https://nla.gov.au/nla.obj-232223665</ref>.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am not going to report specially on<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Giles's last remarkable journey, because the printed reports will<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>reach<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>you<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>more quickly<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from the closer Swan River<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. Perth, WA.</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The map of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Ernest<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Giles's expedition had already been sent to Petermann from Adelaide; see G. Goyder to M, 31 December 1875.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>than I<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>could<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>give<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>them<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>from here. The enclosed letter of the worthy Mr Elder<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See T. Elder to M, 21 December<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1875 (in this edition as 75-12-21a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>will, however, interest you.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Always<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>respectfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="margin-left: 1.75in; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
      </body>
